                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14439169" author="bentmann" created="Fri, 1 Aug 2008 08:58:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;From &lt;tt&gt;AbstractJavadocMojo.java:1471&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// ----------------------------------------------------------------------
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Javadoc output directory as File
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// ----------------------------------------------------------------------
&lt;/span&gt;
File javadocOutputDirectory = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; File( getOutputDirectory() );
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ( javadocOutputDirectory.exists() &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !javadocOutputDirectory.isDirectory() )
{
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; MavenReportException( &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;IOException: &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + getOutputDirectory() + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot; is not a directory.&quot;&lt;/span&gt; );
}
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ( javadocOutputDirectory.exists() &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !javadocOutputDirectory.canWrite() )
{
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; MavenReportException( &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;IOException: &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + getOutputDirectory() + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot; is not writable.&quot;&lt;/span&gt; );
}
javadocOutputDirectory.mkdirs();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i.e. there is already a call to {{mkdirs()}. So I wonder whether this issue was really present or just a side effect of the (still present) failures with RC4.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14439007" author="siveton" created="Fri, 1 Aug 2008 08:58:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This was already catched in the AbstractJavadocMojo#executeReport( Locale unusedLocale ) &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;...
        File javadocOutputDirectory = new File( getOutputDirectory() );
        if ( javadocOutputDirectory.exists() &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !javadocOutputDirectory.isDirectory() )
        {
            throw new MavenReportException( &quot;IOException: &quot; + getOutputDirectory() + &quot; is not a directory.&quot; );
        }
        if ( javadocOutputDirectory.exists() &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !javadocOutputDirectory.canWrite() )
        {
            throw new MavenReportException( &quot;IOException: &quot; + getOutputDirectory() + &quot; is not writable.&quot; );
        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, if the output was not created the javadoc plugin should failed. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyway, your commit is a safe one. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14439099" author="bentmann" created="Fri, 1 Aug 2008 09:04:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Crazy timing....&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Anyway, your commit is a safe one. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Getters with side-effects, hm...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14439028" author="brettporter" created="Fri, 1 Aug 2008 09:10:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the report directory (target/site/apidocs) is not the same as the output directory considered above (target/apidocs). While it should already exist, it&apos;s best for the plugin to act independently.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll move it from the getter to the execute method thogh.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14439119" author="brettporter" created="Fri, 1 Aug 2008 09:15:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ah, now I see it&apos;s assigning to the protected outputDirectory. That is confusing &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; Sorry about that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14439150" author="siveton" created="Fri, 1 Aug 2008 09:17:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FYI the output mkdir is handle by the javadoc tool itself&lt;br/&gt;
See &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.docjar.com/docs/api/com/sun/tools/doclets/internal/toolkit/Configuration.html#generalValidOptions(String,%20DocErrorReporter&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.docjar.com/docs/api/com/sun/tools/doclets/internal/toolkit/Configuration.html#generalValidOptions(String,%20DocErrorReporter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;...
                if (!destDir.exists()) {
                    //Create the output directory (in case it doesn&apos;t exist yet)
                    reporter.printNotice(getText(&quot;doclet.dest_dir_create&quot;,
                        destdirname));
                    (new File(destdirname)).mkdirs();

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14439181" author="siveton" created="Fri, 1 Aug 2008 09:18:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;bq: ah, now I see it&apos;s assigning to the protected outputDirectory. That is confusing  Sorry about that. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is why we have &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-205&quot; title=&quot;Review output directory for Javadoc reports (main and test) and jar (main and test)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MJAVADOC-205&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MJAVADOC-205&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17957589" author="olamy" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2025 03:44:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/issues/1004&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven-javadoc-plugin#1004&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
